## **Conclusion**

This lab introduced the concept of **one-dimensional arrays** and demonstrated how loops can be used to efficiently access, modify, and process array elements in C programming.

Understanding **arrays and loops** is essential for handling large datasets and building structured and efficient programs. The lab also explored **character arrays and scansets**, which are useful techniques for handling user input and string data in C.
